at the door or a window

00:25:44.170 --> 00:25:45.760 align:middle line:90%
before the person gets home.

00:25:45.760 --> 00:25:51.810 align:middle line:90%


00:25:51.810 --> 00:25:54.480 align:middle line:84%
We've done experiments that
show it is really happening.

00:25:54.480 --> 00:25:57.330 align:middle line:84%
We filmed the place
with the dog waits.

00:25:57.330 --> 00:26:00.240 align:middle line:84%
We have people go at
least five miles away.

00:26:00.240 --> 00:26:02.550 align:middle line:84%
We have them come to
him at random times.

00:26:02.550 --> 00:26:06.210 align:middle line:10%
They travel by taxi to
avoid familiar car sounds,

00:26:06.210 --> 00:26:07.260 align:middle line:10%
and the dogs still know.

00:26:07.260 --> 00:26:10.400 align:middle line:10%
They start waiting when the
person decides to go home.

00:26:10.400 --> 00:26:13.500 align:middle line:84%
So they're responding to
the person's intention.

00:26:13.500 --> 00:26:16.770 align:middle line:10%
And, therefore, it seems to
be a psychopathic phenomena.

00:26:16.770 --> 00:26:20.290 align:middle line:10%
It's what's going on in the
person's mind, not noises

00:26:20.290 --> 00:26:23.194 align:middle line:10%
or physical clues or
anything like that's telling

00:26:23.194 --> 00:26:24.360 align:middle line:10%
the dog when they're coming.

00:26:24.360 --> 00:26:36.890 align:middle line:90%


00:26:36.890 --> 00:26:40.470 align:middle line:84%
I think social groups of
animals have morphic fields--

00:26:40.470 --> 00:26:44.970 align:middle line:84%
termite nests, ants' nests,
bees' hives and flocks of birds

00:26:44.970 --> 00:26:46.950 align:middle line:90%
and schools of fish do as well.

00:26:46.950 --> 00:26:51.600 align:middle line:84%
The whole group behaves as
if they're a single organism.

00:26:51.600 --> 00:26:54.600 align:middle line:84%
I think all social
animals, including us,

00:26:54.600 --> 00:26:58.080 align:middle line:84%
have fields for social groups
that link the members together

00:26:58.080 --> 00:27:00.450 align:middle line:84%
within the group and
continues to connect

00:27:00.450 --> 00:27:02.130 align:middle line:84%
and even when they're
away from each

00:27:02.130 --> 00:27:06.480 align:middle line:90%
other, physically separated.

00:27:06.480 --> 00:27:09.030 align:middle line:84%
The closest physical
analogy to telepathy

00:27:09.030 --> 00:27:13.556 align:middle line:84%
is in quantum physics,
quantum non-locality.

00:27:13.556 --> 00:27:15.930 align:middle line:84%
Quantum non-locality mechanics
is when two particles have

00:27:15.930 --> 00:27:17.340 align:middle line:90%
been part of the same system.

00:27:17.340 --> 00:27:20.640 align:middle line:10%
They're part of the same
system, they move apart,

00:27:20.640 --> 00:27:22.200 align:middle line:10%
and when they move
apart, they remain

00:27:22.200 --> 00:27:25.350 align:middle line:10%
linked to each
other or entangled

00:27:25.350 --> 00:27:27.610 align:middle line:10%
as quantum physicists say.

00:27:27.610 --> 00:27:30.450 align:middle line:10%
And so that a change in one
instantly affects the other.

00:27:30.450 --> 00:27:40.970 align:middle line:90%


00:27:40.970 --> 00:27:43.700 align:middle line:84%
My idea of morphic fields
is very similar in spirit

00:27:43.700 --> 00:27:44.650 align:middle line:90%
to quantum theory.

00:27:44.650 --> 00:27:47.090 align:middle line:84%
The morphic fields are a
bit like quantum field.

00:27:47.090 --> 00:27:48.680 align:middle line:90%
They're probability structures.

00:27:48.680 --> 00:27:51.710 align:middle line:84%
Nature is organized
by invisible fields.

00:27:51.710 --> 00:27:54.920 align:middle line:84%
Living organisms are
organized by invisible fields.

00:27:54.920 --> 00:27:56.630 align:middle line:84%
This seems to be the
nature of nature.

00:27:56.630 --> 00:28:03.300 align:middle line:90%


00:28:03.300 --> 00:28:06.760 align:middle line:84%
>> Telepathy suggests a form
of connection between people.

00:28:06.760 --> 00:28:09.660 align:middle line:84%
So if two people are really
connected, then if you separate

00:28:09.660 --> 00:28:11.380 align:middle line:90%
them and you poke one of them.

00:28:11.380 --> 00:28:13.050 align:middle line:90%
The other one should flinch.

00:28:13.050 --> 00:28:15.630 align:middle line:10%
And one of the more
interesting studies

00:28:15.630 --> 00:28:17.130 align:middle line:10%
of this type that
I know of was told

00:28:17.130 --> 00:28:20.370 align:middle line:10%
by colleagues at
Bastyr University

00:28:20.370 --> 00:28:21.840 align:middle line:10%
and the University
of Washington.

00:28:21.840 --> 00:28:25.770 align:middle line:10%
They selected one couple
out of 30 couples,

00:28:25.770 --> 00:28:27.450 align:middle line:10%
and then they put
the person playing

00:28:27.450 --> 00:28:30.644 align:middle line:10%
the role of a receiver
in a functional MRI.

00:28:30.644 --> 00:28:32.810 align:middle line:84%
This is a scanner that's
looking at what's happening

00:28:32.810 --> 00:28:34.580 align:middle line:90%
in the blood flow in your head.

00:28:34.580 --> 00:28:36.630 align:middle line:84%
And they put the other
person at a distance

00:28:36.630 --> 00:28:40.590 align:middle line:84%
and expose the descending
person to flashing lights

00:28:40.590 --> 00:28:41.826 align:middle line:90%
or static lights.

00:28:41.826 --> 00:28:43.950 align:middle line:84%
And the question was if
these two people are really

00:28:43.950 --> 00:28:46.420 align:middle line:84%
connected mentally,
then when one person

00:28:46.420 --> 00:28:49.020 align:middle line:84%
is seeing flashing lights,
maybe the brain of the other one

00:28:49.020 --> 00:28:50.659 align:middle line:90%
will light up as well.

00:28:50.659 --> 00:28:52.200 align:middle line:84%
So they did this
experiment, and they

00:28:52.200 --> 00:28:54.417 align:middle line:84%
found that the receiver's
brain was lighting up.

00:28:54.417 --> 00:28:56.250 align:middle line:84%
And it was lighting up
in the visual cortex.

00:28:56.250 --> 00:29:00.950 align:middle line:90%


00:29:00.950 --> 00:29:03.460 align:middle line:84%
This actually not only
shows that telepathy

00:29:03.460 --> 00:29:05.410 align:middle line:84%
is real under highly
controlled conditions,

00:29:05.410 --> 00:29:07.270 align:middle line:84%
it tells us a little
bit about the nature

00:29:07.270 --> 00:29:09.850 align:middle line:90%
of what that connection is.

00:29:09.850 --> 00:29:11.590 align:middle line:84%
It would be very, very
unlikely that it's

00:29:11.590 --> 00:29:14.976 align:middle line:84%
a kind of signal
connection, meaning

00:29:14.976 --> 00:29:17.350 align:middle line:84%
like a radio sending a signal
from one place to the other

00:29:17.350 --> 00:29:18.460 align:middle line:90%
because.

00:29:18.460 --> 00:29:21.490 align:middle line:84%
The usual form of
signaling was excluded.

00:29:21.490 --> 00:29:24.050 align:middle line:84%
So instead if two
brains are, in a sense,

00:29:24.050 --> 00:29:26.424 align:middle line:84%
almost acting like
one, it suggests

00:29:26.424 --> 00:29:28.090 align:middle line:84%
that the connections
we're talking about

00:29:28.090 --> 00:29:30.980 align:middle line:90%
are a holistic connection.

00:29:30.980 --> 00:29:34.510 align:middle line:84%
And I think that that begins
to point more towards a quantum

00:29:34.510 --> 00:29:38.286 align:middle line:84%
connection rather than any
form of classical connection.

00:29:38.286 --> 00:29:47.330 align:middle line:90%


00:29:47.330 --> 00:29:51.770 align:middle line:84%
>> I was approached by the
grandmother of a nine-month-old

00:29:51.770 --> 00:29:54.290 align:middle line:90%
child that had been taken.

00:29:54.290 --> 00:29:57.170 align:middle line:84%
There was a divorce
situation going on,

00:29:57.170 --> 00:30:01.190 align:middle line:84%
so they brought me pictures
and the baby's teddy bear.

00:30:01.190 --> 00:30:03.710 align:middle line:84%
And I started-- it was
kind of difficult because I

00:30:03.710 --> 00:30:05.870 align:middle line:90%
go through thought patterns.

00:30:05.870 --> 00:30:09.740 align:middle line:84%
And because he's nine months
old and he's in a car seat,

00:30:09.740 --> 00:30:11.270 align:middle line:90%
he can't see out the windows.

00:30:11.270 --> 00:30:15.230 align:middle line:84%
So all I can see is the inside
of the cab of the truck.

00:30:15.230 --> 00:30:18.200 align:middle line:84%
And so I would keep track
of it over a period of days.

00:30:18.200 --> 00:30:22.810 align:middle line:84%
And then one morning I got
up and I called the officer

00:30:22.810 --> 00:30:24.270 align:middle line:90%
that I was working with.

00:30:24.270 --> 00:30:27.260 align:middle line:84%
And I said he's with this
lady, and I described

00:30:27.260 --> 00:30:29.060 align:middle line:90%
what the lady looked like.

00:30:29.060 --> 00:30:33.440 align:middle line:84%
And they're going to go to a
grocery store this morning.

00:30:33.440 --> 00:30:35.840 align:middle line:84%
And I described what the
grocery store looked like

00:30:35.840 --> 00:30:37.760 align:middle line:90%
and where was.

00:30:37.760 --> 00:30:40.880 align:middle line:84%
He figured out who the woman
was that I was talking about.

00:30:40.880 --> 00:30:45.290 align:middle line:84%
It was the sister of the
man who had taken the baby.

00:30:45.290 --> 00:30:47.840 align:middle line:84%
So they spent the
morning, all these agents,

00:30:47.840 --> 00:30:51.530 align:middle line:84%
walking around the grocery
store pretending to shop,

00:30:51.530 --> 00:30:53.000 align:middle line:90%
waiting for her to show up.

00:30:53.000 --> 00:30:56.270 align:middle line:84%
And then she showed up,
she had the baby with her.

00:30:56.270 --> 00:30:57.710 align:middle line:84%
And they were
trying to figure out

00:30:57.710 --> 00:31:01.850 align:middle line:84%
what to do when she
walked away and left

00:31:01.850 --> 00:31:06.020 align:middle line:84%
the nine-month-old
unattended in a grocery cart.

00:31:06.020 --> 00:31:09.740 align:middle line:84%
And the agents just swooped down
on the cart and rolled it away.

00:31:09.740 --> 00:31:12.260 align:middle line:84%
And they arrested her
as a co-conspirator

00:31:12.260 --> 00:31:16.020 align:middle line:90%
for kidnapping the baby.

00:31:16.020 --> 00:31:18.210 align:middle line:84%
If I'm working from
crime scene photos, which

00:31:18.210 --> 00:31:21.240 align:middle line:84%
is the way I prefer to
work, then the event

00:31:21.240 --> 00:31:24.270 align:middle line:84%
itself starts
re-running in my head.

00:31:24.270 --> 00:31:27.890 align:middle line:84%
It's like a movie that's
been very poorly edited.

00:31:27.890 --> 00:31:29.940 align:middle line:84%
The sound doesn't
work very well.

00:31:29.940 --> 00:31:34.260 align:middle line:84%
And I can get snippets of
sound, a little short running

00:31:34.260 --> 00:31:36.450 align:middle line:84%
sequence, and then
there'll be a gap.

00:31:36.450 --> 00:31:39.750 align:middle line:84%
And it's like watching
a poor quality movie,

00:31:39.750 --> 00:31:43.050 align:middle line:84%
but I've learned how to
rerun images many times,

00:31:43.050 --> 00:31:45.780 align:middle line:84%
so that if a police
officer asks me a question,

00:31:45.780 --> 00:31:47.590 align:middle line:90%
I can rerun the image.

00:31:47.590 --> 00:31:50.370 align:middle line:84%
Look at it from
an adjusted angle

00:31:50.370 --> 00:31:53.200 align:middle line:84%
and get the information
they're asking me for.

00:31:53.200 --> 00:31:55.630 align:middle line:84%
So I am technically
doing remote viewing,

00:31:55.630 --> 00:31:57.630 align:middle line:84%
although most people don't
think of it that way.

00:31:57.630 --> 00:32:12.430 align:middle line:90%


00:32:12.430 --> 00:32:14.710 align:middle line:84%
>> Remote viewing is
the scientific term

00:32:14.710 --> 00:32:19.000 align:middle line:84%
for clairvoyance-- using our
sixth sense to get information

00:32:19.000 --> 00:32:22.230 align:middle line:90%
about a distant place or object.

00:32:22.230 --> 00:32:25.450 align:middle line:84%
>> I was a straightforward
laser physicist at Stanford

00:32:25.450 --> 00:32:26.520 align:middle line:90%
University.

00:32:26.520 --> 00:32:28.510 align:middle line:90%
I graduated with my PhD there.

00:32:28.510 --> 00:32:34.180 align:middle line:10%
And then I worked on a textbook,
a graduate level textbook

00:32:34.180 --> 00:32:37.097 align:middle line:10%
on quantum electronics
and lasers.

00:32:37.097 --> 00:32:39.430 align:middle line:10%
And there's nothing like
writing a textbook on a subject

00:32:39.430 --> 00:32:42.190 align:middle line:10%
to realize how much
you don't know.

00:32:42.190 --> 00:32:44.320 align:middle line:84%
And one of the
things that struck me

00:32:44.320 --> 00:32:46.540 align:middle line:84%
as I was working on
the book was that we

00:32:46.540 --> 00:32:48.430 align:middle line:84%
had a pretty good
quantum description

00:32:48.430 --> 00:32:54.380 align:middle line:84%
of all kinds of mechanistic
inorganic interactions.

00:32:54.380 --> 00:32:55.810 align:middle line:84%
But we don't have
a quantum theory

00:32:55.810 --> 00:33:02.650 align:middle line:84%
