was to see somebody

00:48:42.830 --> 00:48:44.720 align:middle line:84%
do something that
could not be done

00:48:44.720 --> 00:48:46.520 align:middle line:84%
through the use
of ordinary force

00:48:46.520 --> 00:48:48.566 align:middle line:90%
by trick or by any other means.

00:48:48.566 --> 00:48:49.940 align:middle line:84%
And what I was
hoping to find was

00:48:49.940 --> 00:48:52.790 align:middle line:84%
somebody who could take
the bowl of a soup spoon

00:48:52.790 --> 00:48:53.840 align:middle line:90%
and bend it in half.

00:48:53.840 --> 00:48:58.460 align:middle line:90%


00:48:58.460 --> 00:49:01.460 align:middle line:84%
So I knew a woman
who was at this party

00:49:01.460 --> 00:49:04.290 align:middle line:84%
and who had claimed to do
things like this in the past.

00:49:04.290 --> 00:49:07.380 align:middle line:84%
So I sat down within two feet
of her, watching her carefully,

00:49:07.380 --> 00:49:09.740 align:middle line:84%
and was holding
a spoon of my own

00:49:09.740 --> 00:49:11.990 align:middle line:84%
and was mimicking what
she was doing just

00:49:11.990 --> 00:49:14.860 align:middle line:84%
to get a kinesthetic feel
for what was going on.

00:49:14.860 --> 00:49:16.780 align:middle line:90%
>> Buckle!

00:49:16.780 --> 00:49:18.840 align:middle line:90%
Buckle, buckle, buckle.

00:49:18.840 --> 00:49:22.760 align:middle line:84%
>> I guess I got to get
my brain out of the way.

00:49:22.760 --> 00:49:25.250 align:middle line:84%
>> So she was trying this for
a couple of minutes and I was

00:49:25.250 --> 00:49:27.710 align:middle line:90%
watching her intently.

00:49:27.710 --> 00:49:29.951 align:middle line:84%
And then somebody behind
me said look what you did.

00:49:29.951 --> 00:49:31.950 align:middle line:84%
And they were talking
about me, what I had done.

00:49:31.950 --> 00:49:34.880 align:middle line:84%
And what I did is I had
bent the bowl of the spoon

00:49:34.880 --> 00:49:37.527 align:middle line:90%
about 90 degrees over.

00:49:37.527 --> 00:49:39.110 align:middle line:84%
And I immediately
looked at my fingers

00:49:39.110 --> 00:49:42.140 align:middle line:84%
to see if I had been applying
pressure because it would have

00:49:42.140 --> 00:49:44.490 align:middle line:90%
let an indentation to do it.

00:49:44.490 --> 00:49:46.830 align:middle line:84%
And there wasn't any
indication of that at all.

00:49:46.830 --> 00:49:49.310 align:middle line:84%
So someone said, well,
bend it all the way.

00:49:49.310 --> 00:49:52.220 align:middle line:84%
I said, OK, so I just
pushed it with one finger,

00:49:52.220 --> 00:49:53.930 align:middle line:84%
and it just went
all the way over.

00:49:53.930 --> 00:49:58.100 align:middle line:84%
It felt soft like taffy and
pinched over and immediately

00:49:58.100 --> 00:50:03.214 align:middle line:84%
hardened up, and it's
been that way to this day.

00:50:03.214 --> 00:50:04.166 align:middle line:90%
>> Buckle!

00:50:04.166 --> 00:50:05.118 align:middle line:90%
>> Buckle.

00:50:05.118 --> 00:50:05.594 align:middle line:90%
>> Buckle!

00:50:05.594 --> 00:50:06.546 align:middle line:90%
>> Buckle.

00:50:06.546 --> 00:50:07.974 align:middle line:90%
>> Go ahead.

00:50:07.974 --> 00:50:11.370 align:middle line:90%


00:50:11.370 --> 00:50:12.770 align:middle line:90%
I hate to do it for people.

00:50:12.770 --> 00:50:16.290 align:middle line:84%
>> No, I'd like to
do it for myself.

00:50:16.290 --> 00:50:18.660 align:middle line:90%
>> Why is it so quiet?

00:50:18.660 --> 00:50:21.555 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:50:21.555 --> 00:50:22.355 align:middle line:90%
>> Do it.

00:50:22.355 --> 00:50:24.310 align:middle line:90%
Now, come on.

00:50:24.310 --> 00:50:26.340 align:middle line:90%
Do it, now come on.

00:50:26.340 --> 00:50:27.140 align:middle line:90%
Go!

00:50:27.140 --> 00:50:38.996 align:middle line:90%


00:50:38.996 --> 00:50:41.960 align:middle line:90%
[CHEERS]

00:50:41.960 --> 00:50:43.442 align:middle line:90%


00:50:43.442 --> 00:50:45.418 align:middle line:90%
>> Hey!

00:50:45.418 --> 00:50:47.820 align:middle line:90%
>> How do I do that?

00:50:47.820 --> 00:50:49.762 align:middle line:90%
>> Got my brain out of the way.

00:50:49.762 --> 00:50:51.530 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:50:51.530 --> 00:50:52.414 align:middle line:90%


00:50:52.414 --> 00:50:55.997 align:middle line:84%
>> I don't know, just all
of sudden I was just--

00:50:55.997 --> 00:50:58.680 align:middle line:90%


00:50:58.680 --> 00:51:01.460 align:middle line:84%
an intuitive feeling, kind
of like if make a jumper

00:51:01.460 --> 00:51:05.630 align:middle line:84%
on shot on the basketball court
when playing a basketball game.

00:51:05.630 --> 00:51:06.722 align:middle line:90%
Something like that.

00:51:06.722 --> 00:51:07.864 align:middle line:90%
>> In the the zone?

00:51:07.864 --> 00:51:11.998 align:middle line:84%
>> Exactly I used to be
able to there a lot faster.

00:51:11.998 --> 00:51:13.339 align:middle line:90%
>> Did you buckle?

00:51:13.339 --> 00:51:17.960 align:middle line:90%


00:51:17.960 --> 00:51:20.420 align:middle line:84%
>> The problem with it from
a scientific point of view is

00:51:20.420 --> 00:51:24.020 align:middle line:84%
it's extremely difficult to
capture this under conditions

00:51:24.020 --> 00:51:27.524 align:middle line:84%
that are controlled well
enough so that you can provide

00:51:27.524 --> 00:51:29.690 align:middle line:84%
evidence to somebody else
to show that it looks like

00:51:29.690 --> 00:51:32.194 align:middle line:84%
it's real because I can't
do that with my spoon.

00:51:32.194 --> 00:51:33.860 align:middle line:84%
And I don't even make
the claim of that.

00:51:33.860 --> 00:51:36.440 align:middle line:84%
I don't expect
anybody to believe it,

00:51:36.440 --> 00:51:40.310 align:middle line:84%
but I have my own experience now
where I know I can believe it.

00:51:40.310 --> 00:51:45.060 align:middle line:84%
So when it comes to the rules
of evidence and science,

00:51:45.060 --> 00:51:47.660 align:middle line:90%
it doesn't have much currency.

00:51:47.660 --> 00:51:50.100 align:middle line:84%
When it comes to a
personal experience,

00:51:50.100 --> 00:51:52.230 align:middle line:90%
there's a lot of currency.

00:51:52.230 --> 00:51:57.050 align:middle line:84%
>> Psycho-kinesis, or in short
PK, means mind over matter.

00:51:57.050 --> 00:52:00.360 align:middle line:84%
Can we humans through the
power of our mind's intention

00:52:00.360 --> 00:52:02.210 align:middle line:90%
affect anything?

00:52:02.210 --> 00:52:05.770 align:middle line:84%
>> Psycho-kinesis, the original
classical experiments used

00:52:05.770 --> 00:52:07.100 align:middle line:90%
dice.

00:52:07.100 --> 00:52:09.650 align:middle line:10%
They were triggered by
professional gambler

00:52:09.650 --> 00:52:12.980 align:middle line:10%
who came in to JB Ryan's
laboratory at Duke University

00:52:12.980 --> 00:52:14.060 align:middle line:10%
once.

00:52:14.060 --> 00:52:17.360 align:middle line:84%
And said I'm a professional
gambler and I shoot craps

00:52:17.360 --> 00:52:20.390 align:middle line:84%
and I make a good living at it,
but I read the statistics book

00:52:20.390 --> 00:52:22.880 align:middle line:84%
recently and I found
that I can't possibly

00:52:22.880 --> 00:52:24.920 align:middle line:84%
make the kind of living
I do without cheating.

00:52:24.920 --> 00:52:26.540 align:middle line:90%
What's happening?

00:52:26.540 --> 00:52:29.390 align:middle line:10%
And so they tested
it and asked him

00:52:29.390 --> 00:52:31.640 align:middle line:10%
to will certain
dice face to come up

00:52:31.640 --> 00:52:32.720 align:middle line:10%
that would make him win.

00:52:32.720 --> 00:52:35.180 align:middle line:10%
And he got them more
often than chance.

00:52:35.180 --> 00:52:37.700 align:middle line:10%
And this evolved into a
regular testing procedure

00:52:37.700 --> 00:52:41.060 align:middle line:10%
where eventually machines
would throw these dice

00:52:41.060 --> 00:52:44.300 align:middle line:10%
while people were told make
the sixes come up this time.

00:52:44.300 --> 00:52:45.170 align:middle line:90%
OK, thank you.

00:52:45.170 --> 00:52:47.420 align:middle line:84%
Now make the fives
come up this time.

00:52:47.420 --> 00:52:50.030 align:middle line:84%
And again, people got
scores different from chance

00:52:50.030 --> 00:52:53.690 align:middle line:84%
enough to know that sometimes
the mind can reach out

00:52:53.690 --> 00:52:57.050 align:middle line:84%
directly affect the state of
matter in these rolling dice.

00:52:57.050 --> 00:52:59.090 align:middle line:84%
Nobody tests with
dice nowadays, they

00:52:59.090 --> 00:53:01.310 align:middle line:84%
use fancy electronic
machines which

00:53:01.310 --> 00:53:04.790 align:middle line:84%
are even harder to imagine what
in the world they could do.

00:53:04.790 --> 00:53:08.150 align:middle line:90%


00:53:08.150 --> 00:53:11.750 align:middle line:84%
>> Scientists have created
ever more sophisticated methods

00:53:11.750 --> 00:53:13.520 align:middle line:90%
of measuring chance.

00:53:13.520 --> 00:53:15.890 align:middle line:90%
First, they built this machine.

00:53:15.890 --> 00:53:19.940 align:middle line:10%
It takes 9000 plastic
marbles up a conveyor belt

00:53:19.940 --> 00:53:22.580 align:middle line:10%
and then randomly drops them.

00:53:22.580 --> 00:53:26.840 align:middle line:10%
Normally, they fall into
a bell shaped curve.

00:53:26.840 --> 00:53:31.120 align:middle line:84%
So a scientist asked everyday
people, students and so forth,

00:53:31.120 --> 00:53:34.370 align:middle line:84%
to mentally will more
balls to fall to the left

00:53:34.370 --> 00:53:36.230 align:middle line:90%
or to fall to the right.

00:53:36.230 --> 00:53:38.440 align:middle line:84%
And they successfully
managed to do so.

00:53:38.440 --> 00:53:41.090 align:middle line:90%


00:53:41.090 --> 00:53:45.090 align:middle line:84%
Then they did the same test
with this swinging pendulum.

00:53:45.090 --> 00:53:47.780 align:middle line:84%
Again, people were
able to significantly

00:53:47.780 --> 00:53:50.570 align:middle line:90%
increase or decrease its swing.

00:53:50.570 --> 00:53:53.720 align:middle line:84%
>> The issue is what kind of
control do we have to know

00:53:53.720 --> 00:53:54.900 align:middle line:90%
what's going on.

00:53:54.900 --> 00:53:57.260 align:middle line:10%
So in the laboratory,
rather than in using spoons,

00:53:57.260 --> 00:53:59.870 align:middle line:10%
we'll use something
more like a system which

00:53:59.870 --> 00:54:03.650 align:middle line:10%
is extremely sensitive to
any type of external force

00:54:03.650 --> 00:54:05.670 align:middle line:10%
like the movement of electrons.

00:54:05.670 --> 00:54:08.370 align:middle line:84%
So here we have a
random number generator.

00:54:08.370 --> 00:54:13.040 align:middle line:84%
You can see it's a fairly
simple electrical circuit.

00:54:13.040 --> 00:54:17.270 align:middle line:84%
It goes through the serial
port of a personal computer.

00:54:17.270 --> 00:54:20.820 align:middle line:84%
And all it's doing is randomly
flipping coins about 10,000

00:54:20.820 --> 00:54:21.620 align:middle line:90%
a second.

00:54:21.620 --> 00:54:25.420 align:middle line:90%


00:54:25.420 --> 00:54:28.870 align:middle line:84%
>> Tests have shown that
in some mysterious way,

00:54:28.870 --> 00:54:32.410 align:middle line:84%
the human mind can influence
this little machine to produce

00:54:32.410 --> 00:54:36.880 align:middle line:84%
more 0s or more 1s and
shift it, ever so slightly,

00:54:36.880 --> 00:54:39.010 align:middle line:84%
away from its normal
random course.

00:54:39.010 --> 00:54:44.710 align:middle line:90%


00:54:44.710 --> 00:54:48.050 align:middle line:84%
If one person can affect
a random number generator,

00:54:48.050 --> 00:54:49.950 align:middle line:84%
scientists then wanted
to see what would

00:54:49.950 --> 00:54:54.220 align:middle line:90%
happen with a group of people.

00:54:54.220 --> 00:54:58.000 align:middle line:10%
>> A lot of people who work in
context that involve groups--

00:54:58.000 --> 00:55:00.910 align:middle line:10%
choruses or sports or
anything where you need

00:55:00.910 --> 00:55:02.350 align:middle line:10%
to work with other people--

00:55:02.350 --> 00:55:04.990 align:middle line:10%
occasionally will
report episodes

00:55:04.990 --> 00:55:10.000 align:middle line:10%
when there seems to be a flow
in the group or the whole group

00:55:10.000 --> 00:55:12.740 align:middle line:10%
gets into the zone, and
it just works better.

00:55:12.740 --> 00:55:16.360 align:middle line:10%
It works like a single
organism, and it feels good too.

00:55:16.360 --> 00:55:18.960 align:middle line:10%
And the question is,
well, what is that?

00:55:18.960 --> 00:55:21.370 align:middle line:10%
Did something happen
psychologically that connected

00:55:21.370 --> 00:55:24.020 align:middle line:10%
people, or is it something else?

00:55:24.020 --> 00:55:28.800 align:middle line:10%
So one possibility is that the
group actually does gel way.

00:55:28.800 --> 00:55:31.836 align:middle line:84%
It's almost as though it
becomes a single organism

00:55:31.836 --> 00:55:33.460 align:middle line:84%
as though there's a
moment in which you

00:55:33.460 --> 00:55:35.860 align:middle line:84%
have random things that
sort of come together

00:55:35.860 --> 00:55:36.790 align:middle line:90%
into a kind of order.

00:55:36.790 --> 00:55:42.390 align:middle line:90%


00:55:42.390 --> 00:55:46.110 align:middle line:84%
So late 1997, myself
and a few others

00:55:46.110 --> 00:55:48.510 align:middle line:84%
were talking about these
experiments and saying, well,

00:55:48.510 --> 00:55:51.630 align:middle line:84%
wouldn't it be interesting if we
could measure the entire world

00:55:51.630 --> 00:55:53.350 align:middle line:90%
during large scale events.

00:55:53.350 --> 00:55:57.060 align:middle line:84%
This was after the funeral
of Princess Diana which

00:55:57.060 --> 00:55:59.786 align:middle line:84%
was a worldwide event and
there are many more of these

00:55:59.786 --> 00:56:01.410 align:middle line:84%
now because of the
way the media works.

00:56:01.410 --> 00:56:08.230 align:middle line:90%


00:56:08.230 --> 00:56:11.440 align:middle line:84%
We figured if we had random
number generators located

00:56:11.440 --> 00:56:14.110 align:middle line:84%
around the world
running 24 hours a day

00:56:14.110 --> 00:56:17.652 align:middle line:84%
that we may find that there's
a change in the randomness

00:56:17.652 --> 00:56:19.360 align:middle line:84%
during periods in
which people are paying

00:56:19.360 --> 00:56:22.160 align:middle line:84%
very close attention to
one thing as compared

00:56:22.160 --> 00:56:22.960 align:middle line:90%
to other times.

00:56:22.960 --> 00:56:26.860 align:middle line:90%


00:56:26.860 --> 00:56:28.990 align:middle line:84%
And so we've now been
running this for some years,

00:56:28.990 --> 00:56:31.450 align:middle line:84%
we've had over
200 events so far.

00:56:31.450 --> 00:56:34.600 align:middle line:84%
And the odds against chance
of the change in randomness

00:56:34.600 --> 00:56:37.030 align:middle line:84%
that we see is about
a million to one.

00:56:37.030 --> 00:56:43.840 align:middle line:90%


00:56:43.840 --> 00:56:46.510 align:middle line:10%
>> And so they discovered
something amazing--

00:56:46.510 --> 00:56:48.820 align:middle line:10%
large group events
can mysteriously

00:56:48.820 --> 00:56:51.310 align:middle line:10%
influence these random
number generators

00:56:51.310 --> 00:56:55.810 align:middle line:10%
causing them to veer off
their usual random course.

00:56:55.810 --> 00:56:58.870 align:middle line:84%
This is Roger Nelson, who
was involved in the earliest

00:56:58.870 --> 00:57:01.480 align:middle line:90%
mind over matter experiments.

00:57:01.480 --> 00:57:03.520 align:middle line:84%
Based here at
Princeton University,

00:57:03.520 --> 00:57:06.580 align:middle line:84%
it was he who organized
his scientist friends

00:57:06.580 --> 00:57:08.710 align:middle line:84%
into collecting random
number generator

00:57:08.710 --> 00:57:11.170 align:middle line:90%
data from around the world.

00:57:11.170 --> 00:57:14.610 align:middle line:84%
Thus, was born the Global
Consciousness Project.

00:57:14.610 --> 00:57:19.320 align:middle line:10%
>> We have a huge database now
that includes events like New

00:57:19.320 --> 00:57:21.670 align:middle line:10%
Years every year
when people gath--

00:57:21.670 --> 00:57:24.805 align:middle line:10%
millions and millions of people,
or maybe billions actually,

00:57:24.805 --> 00:57:25.680 align:middle line:10%
celebrate New Year's.

00:57:25.680 --> 00:57:32.344 align:middle line:90%
>> 7, 6, 5, 4, 3, 2, 1!

00:57:32.344 --> 00:57:35.200 align:middle line:90%
Happy New Year!

00:57:35.200 --> 00:57:38.090 align:middle line:84%
>> And people start
counting down.

00:57:38.090 --> 00:57:44.420 align:middle line:84%
They actually focus all together
on this very abstract moment.

00:57:44.420 --> 00:57:45.760 align:middle line:90%
So what we see in the data--

00:57:45.760 --> 00:57:48.100 align:middle line:84%
just consider that we've
got a wandering data

00:57:48.100 --> 00:57:51.550 align:middle line:84%
line that's a composite
across all the time zones

00:57:51.550 --> 00:57:53.680 align:middle line:90%
and all of the REGs.

00:57:53.680 --> 00:57:56.440 align:middle line:84%
The data wander randomly
until about five minutes

00:57:56.440 --> 00:58:01.550 align:middle line:84%
before midnight, and then
the variability decreases.

00:58:01.550 --> 00:58:04.009 align:middle line:84%
And it minimizes around
midnight and then comes back up

00:58:04.009 --> 00:58:05.050 align:middle line:90%
and becomes normal again.

00:58:05.050 --> 00:58:06.910 align:middle line:10%
We have a period of about--

00:58:06.910 --> 00:58:09.750 align:middle line:10%
I think it's on the order of
10 minutes around midnight.

00:58:09.750 --> 00:58:12.730 align:middle line:10%
It looks different
from random, and this

00:58:12.730 --> 00:58:16.983 align:middle line:10%
is consistent enough from year
to year that it's significant.

00:58:16.983 --> 00:58:20.950 align:middle line:90%


00:58:20.950 --> 00:58:25.570 align:middle line:10%
We now have a continuous
record of 65 roughly

00:58:25.570 --> 00:58:29.230 align:middle line:10%
of these devices producing
data from random generators

00:58:29.230 --> 00:58:32.770 align:middle line:10%
scattered around the world,
24 hours a day, 7 days

00:58:32.770 --> 00:58:34.410 align:middle line:10%
a week for years.

00:58:34.410 --> 00:58:37.300 align:middle line:84%
This is a little cloud, we'll
have to turn off very quickly.

00:58:37.300 --> 00:58:42.610 align:middle line:84%
But the size of the bar and
that's loudness of the sound

00:58:42.610 --> 00:58:46.100 align:middle line:84%
is an indication
of the noise level

00:58:46.100 --> 00:58:49.410 align:middle line:90%
at the particular instrument.

00:58:49.410 --> 00:58:53.380 align:middle line:84%
Here's one in the Princeton,
there's one in Holland

00:58:53.380 --> 00:58:54.720 align:middle line:90%
right here.

00:58:54.720 --> 00:58:57.770 align:middle line:84%
21,000, that's a
very big deviation.

00:58:57.770 --> 00:58:59.150 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:58:59.150 --> 00:59:00.400 align:middle line:90%
I'm glad you got one of those.

00:59:00.400 --> 00:59:14.930 align:middle line:90%


00:59:14.930 --> 00:59:17.250 align:middle line:84%
Now there are all
kinds of events.

00:59:17.250 --> 00:59:19.120 align:middle line:10%
There are tragedies, there are--

00:59:19.120 --> 00:59:21.730 align:middle line:10%
wars start and wars end.

00:59:21.730 --> 00:59:24.970 align:middle line:10%
And there are religious
celebrations of various kinds.

00:59:24.970 --> 00:59:29.140 align:middle line:10%
And we have found that if
there are large numbers--

00:59:29.140 --> 00:59:31.660 align:middle line:10%
and that means something like
many hundreds of thousands

00:59:31.660 --> 00:59:34.450 align:middle line:10%
in most cases or millions--

00:59:34.450 --> 00:59:36.680 align:middle line:10%
who become engaged
in the same thing.

00:59:36.680 --> 00:59:40.000 align:middle line:84%
In other words, they kind of
all point the same direction

00:59:40.000 --> 00:59:43.270 align:middle line:84%
