01:25:12.130 --> 01:25:16.620 align:middle line:84%
And years later when the studies
came out supporting prayer,

01:25:16.620 --> 01:25:19.020 align:middle line:84%
I thought back
about that and began

01:25:19.020 --> 01:25:21.870 align:middle line:90%
to ask questions about that.

01:25:21.870 --> 01:25:26.760 align:middle line:84%
I began to look at surveys of
patients whose diseases simply

01:25:26.760 --> 01:25:28.080 align:middle line:90%
went away.

01:25:28.080 --> 01:25:31.050 align:middle line:10%
And one of the questions that
these patients were asked

01:25:31.050 --> 01:25:34.800 align:middle line:10%
was what do you think
accounted for the disappearance

01:25:34.800 --> 01:25:36.490 align:middle line:10%
of your illness.

01:25:36.490 --> 01:25:38.580 align:middle line:10%
Most of these people
would say, well,

01:25:38.580 --> 01:25:41.370 align:middle line:10%
it had something to
do with my thought,

01:25:41.370 --> 01:25:45.510 align:middle line:10%
the way I chose to live my life.

01:25:45.510 --> 01:25:48.900 align:middle line:10%
Most of them would list some
sort of spiritual practice,

01:25:48.900 --> 01:25:50.290 align:middle line:10%
such as prayer.

01:25:50.290 --> 01:25:54.680 align:middle line:10%
75% say that prayer accounted
for why they got well,

01:25:54.680 --> 01:25:57.320 align:middle line:10%
but others would list
things like music,

01:25:57.320 --> 01:25:59.360 align:middle line:10%
doing mental imagery.

01:25:59.360 --> 01:26:01.580 align:middle line:10%
It's almost embarrassing
about the variety

01:26:01.580 --> 01:26:03.330 align:middle line:10%
of things people described.

01:26:03.330 --> 01:26:36.930 align:middle line:90%


01:26:36.930 --> 01:26:39.240 align:middle line:84%
Skeptics say there
is no evidence.

01:26:39.240 --> 01:26:41.400 align:middle line:90%
This is profoundly wrong.

01:26:41.400 --> 01:26:45.180 align:middle line:10%
Currently, there
are about 21 major

01:26:45.180 --> 01:26:48.300 align:middle line:10%
what we call a randomized,
double blind controlled studies

01:26:48.300 --> 01:26:53.220 align:middle line:10%
looking at the role of
healing intentions or prayer,

01:26:53.220 --> 01:26:54.480 align:middle line:10%
if you will.

01:26:54.480 --> 01:26:57.450 align:middle line:84%
People call this
by different terms.

01:26:57.450 --> 01:26:59.370 align:middle line:84%
Obviously, in the Western
world, most people

01:26:59.370 --> 01:27:03.300 align:middle line:84%
associate prayer with a
religion and with a deity,

01:27:03.300 --> 01:27:04.660 align:middle line:90%
but this is not true.

01:27:04.660 --> 01:27:08.298 align:middle line:84%
If you look at other spiritual
traditions around the world.

01:27:08.298 --> 01:27:41.034 align:middle line:90%


01:27:41.034 --> 01:27:45.400 align:middle line:84%
Built in the early 1800s,
The Santuario de Chimayo

01:27:45.400 --> 01:27:47.650 align:middle line:90%
is about 30 miles north of here.

01:27:47.650 --> 01:27:52.810 align:middle line:84%
People attribute all sorts of
healing powers to not the water

01:27:52.810 --> 01:27:57.580 align:middle line:84%
as at Lourdes, but to the dirt
outside this little church.

01:27:57.580 --> 01:27:59.650 align:middle line:84%
So people go and
they get the dirt,

01:27:59.650 --> 01:28:03.880 align:middle line:84%
and they rub it over the area
of the body that needs healing.

01:28:03.880 --> 01:28:05.860 align:middle line:84%
I was at that little
church one day

01:28:05.860 --> 01:28:10.060 align:middle line:84%
and a woman came in, an
elderly Hispanic woman.

01:28:10.060 --> 01:28:12.490 align:middle line:84%
We struck up a conversation,
and she told me

01:28:12.490 --> 01:28:16.420 align:middle line:84%
years before she had come
there in a wheelchair.

01:28:16.420 --> 01:28:20.690 align:middle line:84%
And she prayed to the
Virgin of Guadalupe

01:28:20.690 --> 01:28:21.910 align:middle line:90%
and something happened.

01:28:21.910 --> 01:28:25.520 align:middle line:84%
And she was able to get out of
her wheelchair and walk away.

01:28:25.520 --> 01:28:27.880 align:middle line:84%
So she left her wheelchair
there in gratitude,

01:28:27.880 --> 01:28:32.050 align:middle line:84%
like people leave crutches
at Lourdes and so on.

01:28:32.050 --> 01:28:35.080 align:middle line:84%
And so she made an annual
pilgrimage every year

01:28:35.080 --> 01:28:39.290 align:middle line:84%
to express gratitude
for her healing.

01:28:39.290 --> 01:28:41.390 align:middle line:84%
She just took it as
a matter of fact.

01:28:41.390 --> 01:28:42.820 align:middle line:90%
She wasn't surprised.

01:28:42.820 --> 01:28:46.990 align:middle line:84%
Many people here who have
fantastic faith in the Virgin

01:28:46.990 --> 01:28:49.850 align:middle line:84%
think that this just sort
of goes with the territory.

01:28:49.850 --> 01:28:56.270 align:middle line:90%


01:28:56.270 --> 01:29:00.110 align:middle line:84%
Actually, the prevalent
idea is that good doctors,

01:29:00.110 --> 01:29:04.500 align:middle line:84%
scientifically oriented doctors
don't believe any of this.

01:29:04.500 --> 01:29:06.780 align:middle line:84%
That happens to be
a false picture.

01:29:06.780 --> 01:29:10.620 align:middle line:84%
We know that because of surveys
that have been recently done.

01:29:10.620 --> 01:29:13.480 align:middle line:84%
The best one came
three years ago,

01:29:13.480 --> 01:29:16.800 align:middle line:84%
and it looked over 1,000
physicians around the United

01:29:16.800 --> 01:29:22.500 align:middle line:84%
States asking them their beliefs
about prayer, remote healing,

01:29:22.500 --> 01:29:23.870 align:middle line:90%
and so on.

01:29:23.870 --> 01:29:27.690 align:middle line:10%
75% of these physicians
said that they

01:29:27.690 --> 01:29:30.900 align:middle line:10%
believe that spiritual beliefs
can help people get well.

01:29:30.900 --> 01:29:35.700 align:middle line:10%
74% said that they think
prayer can work at a distance.

01:29:35.700 --> 01:29:39.600 align:middle line:10%
And 55% said they
had actually seen

01:29:39.600 --> 01:29:43.770 align:middle line:10%
results in their own
patients that resembled

01:29:43.770 --> 01:29:45.630 align:middle line:10%
what they call miracles.

01:29:45.630 --> 01:29:48.830 align:middle line:84%
This is not the picture
people have of doctors.

01:29:48.830 --> 01:29:51.390 align:middle line:84%
Here's the explanatory
factor here.

01:29:51.390 --> 01:29:53.640 align:middle line:10%
If you ask doctors
publicly what they believe,

01:29:53.640 --> 01:29:56.700 align:middle line:10%
they will just deny
that this stuff is real.

01:29:56.700 --> 01:30:00.330 align:middle line:10%
But if you ask them anonymously
on surveys where they do not

01:30:00.330 --> 01:30:04.770 align:middle line:10%
have to sign their name, you get
a completely different picture.

01:30:04.770 --> 01:30:07.520 align:middle line:90%


01:30:07.520 --> 01:30:13.570 align:middle line:84%
These are some benches crafted
for a meditation sitting

01:30:13.570 --> 01:30:14.982 align:middle line:90%
circle.

01:30:14.982 --> 01:30:17.958 align:middle line:90%
[CHANTING]

01:30:17.958 --> 01:30:29.890 align:middle line:90%


01:30:29.890 --> 01:30:31.510 align:middle line:84%
I live in a part
of the world where

01:30:31.510 --> 01:30:35.260 align:middle line:84%
the Native American tradition
is quite strong in northern New

01:30:35.260 --> 01:30:36.560 align:middle line:90%
Mexico.

01:30:36.560 --> 01:30:38.350 align:middle line:84%
And I've had the
opportunity to talk

01:30:38.350 --> 01:30:41.830 align:middle line:84%
with many Native American
healers and shamans

01:30:41.830 --> 01:30:46.270 align:middle line:84%
about what they think about
prayer and intentionality.

01:30:46.270 --> 01:30:48.760 align:middle line:84%
And it's taken for
granted in their tradition

01:30:48.760 --> 01:30:50.680 align:middle line:90%
that these things are real.

01:30:50.680 --> 01:30:55.720 align:middle line:84%
They think it quite odd that
we have lost touch with this.

01:30:55.720 --> 01:30:59.890 align:middle line:84%
One shaman I ask you in the
area where I live whether or not

01:30:59.890 --> 01:31:03.490 align:middle line:84%
she believe in prayer, she
said oh, don't ask me that.

01:31:03.490 --> 01:31:05.620 align:middle line:84%
We don't even have
a word for prayer.

01:31:05.620 --> 01:31:07.240 align:middle line:90%
It's just in the air.

01:31:07.240 --> 01:31:09.340 align:middle line:84%
We don't make anything
special out of it.

01:31:09.340 --> 01:31:13.720 align:middle line:84%
You white people want to
fancify this and make something

01:31:13.720 --> 01:31:15.430 align:middle line:90%
really special out of prayer.

01:31:15.430 --> 01:31:17.442 align:middle line:84%
It's just the way
the world works.

01:31:17.442 --> 01:31:26.880 align:middle line:90%


01:31:26.880 --> 01:31:29.730 align:middle line:84%
We know in modern
medicine that many things

01:31:29.730 --> 01:31:34.110 align:middle line:84%
work, although we don't have
an understanding of how.

01:31:34.110 --> 01:31:37.120 align:middle line:84%
A classic example is
the general anesthetics.

01:31:37.120 --> 01:31:39.910 align:middle line:84%
We don't know how
anesthesia really works,

01:31:39.910 --> 01:31:40.990 align:middle line:90%
but we know that it does.

01:31:40.990 --> 01:31:45.410 align:middle line:84%
So we use it in spite of our
ignorance about how it happens.

01:31:45.410 --> 01:31:47.440 align:middle line:84%
We're at pretty much
the same juncture

01:31:47.440 --> 01:31:51.580 align:middle line:90%
with healing from a distance.

01:31:51.580 --> 01:31:55.810 align:middle line:84%
Although there are around 20
major hypotheses about how

01:31:55.810 --> 01:31:58.180 align:middle line:90%
it works, there's no consensus.

01:31:58.180 --> 01:32:01.120 align:middle line:10%
But almost all of
these hypotheses

01:32:01.120 --> 01:32:04.810 align:middle line:10%
suggest we're going to have
to redefine consciousness.

01:32:04.810 --> 01:32:10.370 align:middle line:84%
We're going to have to free it
from the brain, from the body,

01:32:10.370 --> 01:32:13.870 align:middle line:84%
and distribute it, what
I call, non-locally

01:32:13.870 --> 01:32:14.950 align:middle line:90%
out there in the world.

01:32:14.950 --> 01:32:18.359 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

01:32:18.359 --> 01:32:23.720 align:middle line:90%


01:32:23.720 --> 01:32:25.410 align:middle line:84%
I know people get
troubled by the way

01:32:25.410 --> 01:32:27.630 align:middle line:84%
we use the term consciousness
because it's not

01:32:27.630 --> 01:32:30.240 align:middle line:90%
properly defined.

01:32:30.240 --> 01:32:32.070 align:middle line:84%
Because sometimes
in science you have

01:32:32.070 --> 01:32:36.600 align:middle line:84%
to allow a term to
float in ambiguity,

01:32:36.600 --> 01:32:39.360 align:middle line:84%
and you understand its
meaning as you go along.

01:32:39.360 --> 01:32:42.580 align:middle line:84%
And you study how it
manifests in the world,

01:32:42.580 --> 01:32:44.910 align:middle line:84%
then you eventually
can define it.

01:32:44.910 --> 01:32:48.120 align:middle line:84%
That's where we are
with consciousness.

01:32:48.120 --> 01:32:51.840 align:middle line:84%
>> This is where you could
say I keep all my attachments.

01:32:51.840 --> 01:32:54.480 align:middle line:84%
All those things I
probably don't really need,

01:32:54.480 --> 01:32:57.450 align:middle line:84%
but I keep thinking
I need them some day.

01:32:57.450 --> 01:32:59.940 align:middle line:84%
>> By and large science
and spirituality,

01:32:59.940 --> 01:33:03.030 align:middle line:84%
when they come together at all,
are kind of dancing around each

01:33:03.030 --> 01:33:07.870 align:middle line:84%
other and not directly
facing the core issue.

01:33:07.870 --> 01:33:11.460 align:middle line:84%
The core issue is
that most scientists

01:33:11.460 --> 01:33:14.970 align:middle line:84%
are totally married to
an absolute materialist

01:33:14.970 --> 01:33:18.240 align:middle line:84%
philosophy of mind,
which says the mind is

01:33:18.240 --> 01:33:21.450 align:middle line:84%
nothing but chemical
and electrical activity

01:33:21.450 --> 01:33:22.800 align:middle line:90%
in the brain.

01:33:22.800 --> 01:33:25.380 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't reach out
beyond your body.

01:33:25.380 --> 01:33:27.520 align:middle line:90%
It dies when you die.

01:33:27.520 --> 01:33:32.890 align:middle line:84%
That's why I think it's so
important to bring PSI in.

01:33:32.890 --> 01:33:38.200 align:middle line:84%
If materialism is right and
the core basis of spirituality

01:33:38.200 --> 01:33:40.990 align:middle line:84%
is nonsense, the
two are never going

01:33:40.990 --> 01:33:44.650 align:middle line:84%
to help each other it's going
to be a continual fight.

01:33:44.650 --> 01:33:49.000 align:middle line:84%
But if as I see it that when
you apply essential science

01:33:49.000 --> 01:33:51.220 align:middle line:84%
and you discover
these PSI phenomena

01:33:51.220 --> 01:33:55.060 align:middle line:84%
and you find that the mind can
reach beyond the body, that,

01:33:55.060 --> 01:33:57.910 align:middle line:84%
perhaps, it survives
death in some form,

01:33:57.910 --> 01:34:01.060 align:middle line:84%
that we can have
interconnections that are

01:34:01.060 --> 01:34:03.550 align:middle line:90%
extremely deep and pervasive--

01:34:03.550 --> 01:34:06.910 align:middle line:84%
that's much more what genuine
spirituality is about.

01:34:06.910 --> 01:34:09.310 align:middle line:84%
That's where the
marriage between science

01:34:09.310 --> 01:34:11.840 align:middle line:84%
and spirituality
needs to take place.

01:34:11.840 --> 01:34:14.260 align:middle line:84%
I'm trying to build bridges
between those people.

